Commentary Text: T Natarajan to Rinku Singh, out Lbw!! That was plumb and a shocked Nattu literally stood there with his hands on his hips that the finger didn't go up. Eventually it did. Then the batters were discussing. The timer suddenly came down to zero. Both Rinku and Billings were having a chat. Then umpire Anil Kumar Chaudhary said time up. Apparently Billings signalled for the review immediately, but the rule is that the striker has to signal too and Rinku didn't. So the review has been denied. It's only good that it was denied becase that would have smashed the base of middle stump. Outstanding yorker from Nattu. Rinku missed the defence, hits the toe and ball tracker says ball smashing middle and off stump. All that discussion for the review was waste anyway. Rinku Singh lbw b T Natarajan 5(6)

Commentary Text: Umran Malik to Rahane, out Caught by Shashank Singh!! In the airrr, that's a lovely cut shot. Oh it has not gone all the way. Outstanding catch on the fence by Shashank at the deep point boundary. This was a hit me short ball with a lof of width, Rahane thought he could upper cut that, did make good contact and with Umran's pace it looked a six but fielder ran to his right, stretched his hands and pulled it off. Commentary Text: Umran Malik to Nitish Rana, out Caught by Shashank Singh!! It is short but it was definitely not a bouncer. Absolutely poor cricket from Nitish Rana and he is screaming his lungs out on himself. Oh I am expecting one to come to my head kind of movement in the crease from Rana. Simple short of length delivery just outside off stump, Venkatesh thought the cut was on, it would have been on had he made some room.
